This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new method for kernel learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The use of deep architecture and end-to-end training also suggests a connection to deep learning, which is a popular topic in cs.LG. 

The paper also mentions image classification tasks, which suggests a possible connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision). 

The use of flexible kernels and the ability to find suitable kernels for each layer suggests a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and the subfield of kernel methods in AI. 

The mention of overfitting on small datasets suggests a connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which deals with the optimization and generalization of neural networks. 

Finally, the use of Random Fourier Features suggests a connection to cs.SD (Systems and Control), which deals with the design and analysis of control systems, including signal processing and filtering techniques.
